com.impinj.octane

Class Settings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.impinj.octane.Settings

  • public class Settings
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a container class for all of the knobs that control reader behavior. Settings are not applied by changing the values within a class instance. The application must build a class instance (or query the current settings from the reader), modify the class instance, and apply these settings back to the reader. Default settings contain
    • all antennas enabled at max power and sensitivity
    • all gpi enabled with no debounce
    • all gpo enabled in normal mode
    • auto start and stop disabled
    • session 2, dual target, auto-dense reader mode
    • tag reports in individual mode with only an EPC reported
    • keep alive and link monitor disabled
    • low duty cycle disabled
    • no tag inventory filters
    • no tag operation sequences
    • no fast ID enabled
    See Also:
    ImpinjReader.queryDefaultSettings(), ImpinjReader.querySettings(), ImpinjReader.applyDefaultSettings(), ImpinjReader.applySettings(Settings)

      • getSession

        public int getSession()
        Sets the gen2 session for the reader. Gen2 maintains 4 independent sessions so that a tag can be inventoried in several different sessions simultaneously. Also, the session have different persistence properties which change tag read behavior.
        Returns:
        session used by the reader
        See Also:
        Gen2 Standard page 51, Gen2 Standard page 54

      • getHoldReportsOnDisconnect

        public java.lang.Boolean getHoldReportsOnDisconnect()
        When the reader is running an inventory it may be collecting tag reports. If an application disconnects and reconnects, there may be a large number of tag reports. Applications may want to tell the reader to hold on to these reports when the application reconnects so that the application can reconfigure the reader (and even purge these reports).
        Returns:
        true if the reader is set to hold reports on disconnect and reconnect
        See Also:
        ImpinjReader.resumeEventsAndReports()

      • setHoldReportsOnDisconnect

        public void setHoldReportsOnDisconnect(java.lang.Boolean holdReportsOnDisconnect)
        When the reader is running an inventory it may be collecting tag reports. If an application disconnects and reconnects, there may be a large number of tag reports. Applications may want to tell the reader to hold on to these reports when the application reconnects so that the application can reconfigure the reader (and even purge these reports).
        Parameters:
        holdReportsOnDisconnect - set to true to hold reports on disconnect and reconnect.
        See Also:
        ImpinjReader.resumeEventsAndReports()
